4-2 A particle of mass $m_0$ is fixed. Under its gravitational attraction, a particle of mass $m$ moves in a circular orbit of radius $R$. Taking a point $P$ on the circle as the reference point, as shown in Figure 4-2, find:
(1) The torque $M_1$ on particle $m$ due to the gravitational force and the angular momentum $L_1$ of particle $m$ at point 1 in the figure;
(2) The torque $M_2$ on particle $m$ due to the gravitational force and the angular momentum $L_2$ of particle $m$ at point 2 in the figure.
